JOHANNESBURG - American hip-hop artist Chance the Rapper rocked the Dome in Johannesburg on Monday night. The Castle Lite Unlocks Music Experience brought the rapper to the country. Local performances included Shane Eagle, Nadia Nakia and Frank Casino. It was Chance's first performance in South Africa was lapped up by about 10,000 fans. You can watch the insert by eNCA's Ditiro Selepe in the video box above. eNCA